<br>
&quot;- We found and fixed the infamous &quot;Block/Parry bug&quot; - the one that caused players to block and parry less often when attacked by a grouped opponent. This change will have the most effect in RvR situations where you are fighting an opponent who is in a group.&quot;<br>
<br>
Some might say this is a good thing for skalds.  It IS great for Midgard and warriors as they will now actually be able to compete with spearos/LW heros and poleys in real RvR!  However, IMO it is bad for the skald.  With MOST viable skald specs having a 17 parry MAX (before items, RR, MoParry).<br>
<br>
Who feels this will help skalds and why?<br>
<br>
Who feels this weakens us and why?<br>
<br>
IMO, due to only 1.5 spec, it weakens us relative to most other melee hybrids like thanes and champs and pallys who have the spec points to make parry AND/OR block useful.  In terms of hybrids like warden and friar it keeps us even but they already outmeleed and outsupported us.<br>
<br>
I hope someone can point out why this helps us in relation to our melee/support hybrids peers b/c I cant see it.<br>
 <p>Albron<br>
Level 50 Norse Skald<br>
HOOKED on speed!<br>
